{'book': {'publisher': 'Prentice Hall', 'synopsis': 'This in-depth book bridges the gap between educational theory and the classroom with eleven practical classroom management plans designed to be applied to actual teaching situations. Easy to implement, these plans cover two primary circumstances: student on-task and assignment completion problems and student disruptive behavior and rule violations. KEY TOPICS: Written with a minimum of jargon, Classroom Management for All Teachers provides definitions of behavioral terminology and hypothetical examples that demonstrate the effects of specific techniques in a classroom setting. Each plan includes a brief description, baseline measurement tools, step-by-step implementation procedures, hypothetical applications, a selection of reproducible forms, and more. An essential resource for every educator, school administrator, and school psychologist.', 'language': 'en', 'image': 'https://images.isbndb.com/covers/93/32/9780135209332.jpg', 'title_long': 'Classroom Management for All Teachers: 11 Effective Plans', 'edition': '1', 'dimensions': 'Height: 10.82675 Inches, Length: 8.2677 Inches, Weight: 0.85318895394 Pounds, Width: 0.3937 inches', 'dimensions_structured': {'length': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 8.2677}, 'width': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 0.3937}, 'weight': {'unit': 'pounds', 'value': 0.85318895394}, 'height': {'unit': 'inches', 'value': 10.82675}}, 'pages': 168, 'date_published': '1997-10-07', 'subjects': ['Education & Teaching', 'Schools & Teaching', 'Education Theory', 'Instruction Methods', 'Special Education', 'Specialty Boutique', 'New, Used & Rental Textbooks'], 'authors': ['Ennio Cipani'], 'title': 'Classroom Management for All Teachers: 11 Effective Plans', 'isbn13': '9780135209332', 'msrp': 41, 'binding': 'Paperback', 'isbn': '0135209331', 'isbn10': '0135209331'}}